14
00:00:47.660 --> 00:00:51.109
At first, this exercise may
seem quite difficult, even

15
00:00:51.120 --> 00:00:53.239
for an adult, by the way.

16
00:00:53.340 --> 00:00:55.989
Sit the child at the table
and place several objects

17
00:00:56.000 --> 00:00:58.619
of different shapes in front
of them, for example, fruit.

18
00:00:59.210 --> 00:01:02.609
The child taps the table
with their hands, the edge of

19
00:01:02.620 --> 00:01:06.549
the palm in front of a long
object, a fist in front of a

20
00:01:06.560 --> 00:01:10.579
round one, and an open palm
in front of a flat one.

21
00:01:10.640 --> 00:01:13.179
In this example, the
sequence is quite difficult.

22
00:01:13.860 --> 00:01:15.619
We have three
types of objects.

23
00:01:16.240 --> 00:01:19.368
You can simplify the exercise
by reducing the number

24
00:01:19.380 --> 00:01:22.629
of object types to two
or by arranging them

25
00:01:22.640 --> 00:01:23.859
in the same sequence.

26
00:01:24.640 --> 00:01:27.288
If you see that it is
difficult for the child,

27
00:01:27.300 --> 00:01:30.829
support them and start with a
simpler version of the game.

28
00:01:31.480 --> 00:01:35.409
For example, take three
bananas and three tangerines

29
00:01:35.420 --> 00:01:37.489
and place them in the
same sequence for the

30
00:01:37.500 --> 00:01:38.919
right and left hand.

31
00:01:38.960 --> 00:01:42.088
That will make it much easier,
and you can gradually increase

32
00:01:42.100 --> 00:01:43.319
the difficulty of the game.

33
00:01:43.700 --> 00:01:46.148
Then make the sequence
more complex and add

34
00:01:46.160 --> 00:01:47.399
new types of objects.

35
00:01:48.180 --> 00:01:51.239
To feel the progress, play
for five minutes every day.

36
00:01:51.840 --> 00:01:54.508
Have fun, enjoy yourselves,
and try doing the

37
00:01:54.520 --> 00:01:55.219
game yourself.

38
00:02:30.540 --> 00:02:34.249
Draw two geometric shapes on
a sheet of paper, for example,

39
00:02:34.260 --> 00:02:36.059
a triangle and a square.

40
00:02:36.200 --> 00:02:37.809
Circle the corners
of the shapes.

41
00:02:38.380 --> 00:02:41.449
The goal is to move your
fingers simultaneously along

42
00:02:41.460 --> 00:02:42.879
the circles of both shapes.

43
00:02:43.460 --> 00:02:45.569
Here, the child will have
to move the right and

44
00:02:45.580 --> 00:02:48.289
left hand along different
paths, which helps

45
00:02:48.300 --> 00:02:49.999
develop both hemispheres.

46
00:02:50.500 --> 00:02:52.819
At the moment when the
child gets confused...

47
00:02:53.380 --> 00:02:57.349
As you've already noticed,
some exercises seem very

48
00:02:57.360 --> 00:03:00.649
simple, but suddenly
the child gets mixed up

49
00:03:00.660 --> 00:03:02.539
and has to start over.

50
00:03:02.600 --> 00:03:04.319
Don't be discouraged.

51
00:03:04.380 --> 00:03:07.299
A child's brain is very
flexible and learns quickly.

52
00:03:07.760 --> 00:03:10.509
Just keep practicing,
and you will definitely

53
00:03:10.520 --> 00:03:11.539
notice progress.

54
00:03:12.200 --> 00:03:14.749
This exercise is also
best done for five

55
00:03:14.760 --> 00:03:15.859
minutes every day.

56
00:03:16.580 --> 00:03:20.199
If it becomes too easy,
draw more complex shapes.

57
00:05:31.180 --> 00:05:33.589
In this exercise, the child
holds their nose with the

58
00:05:33.600 --> 00:05:36.729
right hand and grabs the
right ear with the left

59
00:05:36.740 --> 00:05:38.779
hand, then alternates hands.

60
00:05:39.320 --> 00:05:42.029
However, before switching
hands, they need to

61
00:05:42.040 --> 00:05:43.329
clap their hands once.

62
00:05:44.180 --> 00:05:47.439
I also recommend that you
try doing this exercise

63
00:05:47.450 --> 00:05:48.599
together with your child.

64
00:05:49.080 --> 00:05:52.209
It seems very simple, but
it will take time before

65
00:05:52.220 --> 00:05:54.239
they can do it quickly
and without mistakes.

66
00:05:54.300 --> 00:05:56.119
That is completely normal.

67
00:05:56.160 --> 00:05:59.819
Do this exercise for three,
five minutes every day.

68
00:07:30.390 --> 00:07:33.369
This exercise is aimed
at fine motor skills.

69
00:07:33.550 --> 00:07:36.849
Here too, both hands need
to make different movements.

70
00:07:37.490 --> 00:07:38.949
Hold your hands
in front of you.

71
00:07:39.690 --> 00:07:43.079
On the right hand, touch the
thumb to the index finger, and

72
00:07:43.090 --> 00:07:46.109
on the left hand, touch the
thumb to the little finger.

73
00:07:46.690 --> 00:07:49.499
Then move the right hand from
the index finger toward the

74
00:07:49.510 --> 00:07:51.899
little finger, touching the
thumb to each next finger

75
00:07:51.910 --> 00:07:54.879
in turn, while the left
hand does the same thing

76
00:07:54.890 --> 00:07:56.829
but in the opposite order.

77
00:07:56.910 --> 00:08:00.109
It is important to move
the fingers simultaneously.

78
00:08:00.150 --> 00:08:02.119
In this exercise,
the difficulty is

79
00:08:02.130 --> 00:08:03.229
adjusted by speed.

80
00:08:03.730 --> 00:08:06.879
If it is hard, do it more
slowly, and if it becomes

81
00:08:06.890 --> 00:08:08.529
too easy, increase the speed.

82
00:08:09.070 --> 00:08:12.099
This exercise will definitely
be easy for those who

83
00:08:12.110 --> 00:08:13.569
play musical instruments.

84
00:08:14.000 --> 00:08:15.809
It is an essential
skill there.

85
00:08:16.610 --> 00:08:19.878
This exercise should also
be practiced daily, but

86
00:08:19.889 --> 00:08:20.989
three minutes is enough.

87
00:08:21.730 --> 00:08:25.219
By the way, you can do it with
your child while traveling or

88
00:08:25.230 --> 00:08:28.769
while waiting in line and need
to keep your child occupied.

89
